eNCA's Michael Marillier reports Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africa is classified as a "water-scarce" nation and experts say climate change is just one part of the problem. Water is one of earth's most important resources, but South Africa's supplies are running low. READ: Limpopo water crisis worsens Farmers are warning of a potential food crisis as the water shortages continue. And the water crisis is just getting worse.